        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4408771868" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18317847792682771672">A lovely supplement to <i>Good to Great.</i><br/><br/>I found it fun to apply several of the key traits of visionary companies to my own life, as well as noticing the company I&apos;m a part of carries all of them.<br/><br/><b>1. Preserves a core ideology—The guiding principles.<br/><br/>2. BHAGs—Big hairy audacious goals.<br/><br/>3. A cult-like culture—In a good, healthy way. (i.e. family.)<br/><br/>4. Consistent innovation—Always trying new things and making adjustments.<br/><br/>5. Promoting within—Encouraging people within the organization to step into leadership.</b></span>
  <span id="freeText18317847792682771672" style="display:none">A lovely supplement to <i>Good to Great.</i><br /><br />I found it fun to apply several of the key traits of visionary companies to my own life, as well as noticing the company I'm a part of carries all of them.<br /><br /><b>1. Preserves a core ideology—The guiding principles.<br /><br />2. BHAGs—Big hairy audacious goals.<br /><br />3. A cult-like culture—In a good, healthy way. (i.e. family.)<br /><br />4. Consistent innovation—Always trying new things and making adjustments.<br /><br />5. Promoting within—Encouraging people within the organization to step into leadership. Not hiring outsiders to lead.</b></span>
